## 🚀 FEATURE WORKFLOW - Order of Operations

### 1️⃣ Triage & Spec (30-60 min)
```markdown
## User Story Template
As a [user type]
I want to [action]
So that [benefit]

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] AC-1: Specific measurable outcome
- [ ] AC-2: Another measurable outcome
- [ ] AC-3: Edge case handling

## Dependencies
- APIs: [List external APIs]
- Database: [Schema changes needed]
- Libraries: [New packages required]
- Feature Flag: `feature_<name>_enabled`

## Observability Plan
- Logs: Key events to log
- Metrics: Counters/timers to add
- Dashboard: Panels to create
```

### 2️⃣ Branch & Scaffold
```bash
# Create feature branch
git checkout -b feat/<scope>-<short-title>

# Generate Nx module/lib if needed
nx g @nx/js:lib features/<feature-name> --tags=scope:feature,type:feature

# Add feature flag (default OFF)
echo "FEATURE_<NAME>_ENABLED=false" >> .env.example
```

### 3️⃣ Test Plan First
```typescript
// Define test cases BEFORE coding

// Unit Tests (Pure/Fast)
describe('FeatureName Core Logic', () => {
  it('should handle happy path')
  it('should validate inputs')
  it('should handle edge cases')
});

// Integration Tests (API ↔ DB)
describe('FeatureName Integration', () => {
  it('should persist data correctly')
  it('should handle concurrent requests')
  it('should respect feature flag')
});

// E2E Test (User Flow)
describe('FeatureName E2E', () => {
  it('should complete user journey when flag enabled')
  it('should gracefully degrade when flag disabled')
});

// Smoke Test (Critical Path)
describe('FeatureName Smoke', () => {
  it('should not break existing flows')
  it('should respond to health check')
});
```

### 4️⃣ Design the Change
```markdown
## ADR Template (if changing patterns)
# ADR-XXX: [Decision Title]

## Status
Proposed | Accepted | Deprecated

## Context
What problem are we solving?

## Decision
What are we doing?

## Consequences
What becomes easier/harder?
```

### 5️⃣ Implement Incrementally (Flag-First)
```typescript
// Always check feature flag first
if (process.env.FEATURE_<NAME>_ENABLED === 'true') {
  // New implementation
  return newFeatureLogic();
} else {
  // Existing behavior
  return existingLogic();
}

// Tracer bullet approach - vertical slice
// 1. Route → 2. Controller → 3. Service → 4. Repository → 5. Database
```

### 6️⃣ Integration & E2E
```bash
# Add integration tests with test containers
docker-compose -f docker-compose.test.yml up -d
nx test <project> --testPathPattern=integration

# Add E2E test behind flag
FEATURE_<NAME>_ENABLED=true nx e2e <project>-e2e
```

### ⚠️ Testing Pitfalls to Avoid

#### Constructor Signature Changes
```typescript
// ❌ Don't test with hard-coded constructor params
const service = new Service({ logger, db, cache });

// ✅ Use dependency injection with mocks
const mockLogger = createMockLogger();
const mockDb = createMockDb();
const service = new Service(mockLogger, mockDb);
```

#### Private Method Testing
```typescript
// ❌ Don't test private methods directly
(service as any).privateMethod();

// ✅ Test public behavior instead
await expect(service.publicMethod()).toThrow('Validation error');
```

#### Node.js Built-in Module Imports
```typescript
// ❌ ES module syntax for Node.js built-ins
import fs from 'fs'; // Fails in Jest

// ✅ Namespace imports for Node.js built-ins
import * as fs from 'fs';
```

#### Mock Typing Issues
```typescript
// ❌ Incorrect mock return types
mockPage.innerText.mockResolvedValue('text'); // Type error

// ✅ Proper type assertions
mockPage.innerText.mockResolvedValue('text' as any);
```

### 7️⃣ Local Affected Checks (Nx)
```bash
# Run all affected checks in parallel
nx affected:lint --parallel
nx affected:test --parallel
nx affected:build --parallel

# If infrastructure changes
nx run <infra-project>:synth
cdk diff
```

### 8️⃣ Open PR Early (Draft)
```markdown
## PR Template
**Title:** feat(scope): short intent

**Summary:** What & why in 2-3 sentences

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] AC-1: Specific outcome
- [ ] AC-2: Another outcome

**Changes:**
- Endpoints: `/api/v1/new-endpoint`
