## 🚨 HOTFIX FAST PATH (Sev-1)

### Immediate Response
```bash
# 1. Create hotfix branch from prod tag
git checkout -b hotfix/<short-title> production-v1.2.3

# 2. Reproduce → Failing test → Minimal fix
npm run test:reproduce-bug

# 3. Fast CI lane (skip non-critical)
nx run-many -t lint,test,build --projects=affected

# 4. Deploy directly to prod
npm run deploy:production:hotfix

# 5. Post-deploy smoke
npm run test:smoke:production

# 6. Monitor for 15-30 minutes
watch -n 5 'curl https://api.example.com/health'

# 7. Back-merge to main
git checkout main
git merge hotfix/<short-title>

# 8. Create postmortem
gh issue create --title "Postmortem: <incident>" \
  --body "Root cause, timeline, action items"
```

