## 🎛️ ROLLOUT & SAFETY PATTERNS

### Feature Flags
```typescript
// Ship dark, test safely, instant rollback
const featureFlag = {
  name: 'feature_x_enabled',
  defaultValue: false,
  rollout: {
    internal: true,
    beta: false,
    production: false
  }
};
```

### Migration Strategy
```typescript
// 1. Deploy forward-compatible code
function readData() {
  return newSchema || oldSchema; // Works with both
}

// 2. Run migration
await runMigration();

// 3. Flip to new path
function readData() {
  return newSchema; // Only new
}

// 4. Remove old code
// Delete oldSchema references
```

### Canary/Blue-Green
```yaml
deployment:
  strategy: canary
  stages:
    - weight: 5%   # 5% traffic
      duration: 1h
    - weight: 25%  # If metrics good
      duration: 2h
    - weight: 100% # Full rollout
```

### Observability
```typescript
// Add instrumentation
const timer = metrics.startTimer('feature_x_duration');
try {
  logger.info('feature_x_started', { userId, timestamp });
  const result = await featureXLogic();
  metrics.increment('feature_x_success');
  return result;
} catch (error) {
  metrics.increment('feature_x_error');
  logger.error('feature_x_failed', { error, userId });
  throw error;
} finally {
  timer.end();
}
```

### Kill Switch
```typescript
// Emergency bypass
if (process.env.KILL_FEATURE_X === 'true') {
  return legacyImplementation();
}
```

